=Drop us a message on mailing lists=

==Mailing Lists @ibiblio==

* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-admin|SM-Admin]] - **[Read Only]** A publically readable list for team member discussion.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-announce|SM-Announce]] - **[Read Only]** The Source Mage GNU/Linux Announce list, publically readable.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-commit|SM-Commit]] - Code commit mailing list.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-discuss|SM-Discuss]] - General Discussion List for Source Mage GNU/Linux. Meant to mirror Admin for non-team members (Non-technical)
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-grimoire|SM-Grimoire]] - This list has been deprecated, but this link will remain for archival purposes. Please use the Discuss list instead.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-grimoire-bugs|SM-Grimoire-Bugs]] - *[Read Only]* list for grimoire bugs that need a wider audience of distribution, possibly for wider discussion.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-security|SM-Security]] - Discuss Source Mage GNU/Linux security issues and keep watch on security bugs.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-sorcery|SM-Sorcery]] - This list has been deprecated, but this link will remain for archival purposes. Please use the Discuss list instead.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-sorcery-bugs|SM-Sorcery-Bugs]] - This list has been deprecated, but this link will remain for archival purposes. Please use the Discuss list instead.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-spell-submit|SM-Spell-Submit]] - A moderated list for receiving announcements about updated software from Source``Forge, Fresh``Meat and other sources.
* [[http://lists.ibiblio.org/mailman/listinfo/sm-users|SM-Users]] - General Discussion List for Source Mage GNU/Linux. A question and answer list. (Technical)

